 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Junior IT Support Specialist Brock Solutions 39 reviews Dallas, TX Full-time Brock Solutions 39 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description A Little Bit About Us 
 
Brock Solutions is an innovative engineering solutions and professional services company specializing in the design, build and implementation of real-time operational solutions for broad based industrial/manufacturing and transportation/logistics organizations worldwide. Some interesting areas we are exploring include industrial automation, machine learning, IIOT, cyber security, AI, robotics, and other technologies. With approximately 600 employees globally, Brock Solutions is a privately held, employee owned organization with over 30 years in the real-time operational solutions space. 
What We Offer 
 
Working with our other highly motivated Developers, you will be involved in the entire cycle of the software engineering process. 
 
Employee-owned company with profit sharing, comprehensive benefits, company events and charitable initiatives, a diverse workplace, BBQs and Lunch & Learns, Sport teams, Group fitness initiatives, and a “Work hard, Play hard” culture are just some of the reasons our employees love working at Brock! 
 
Brock Solutions supports a flexible working environment including options to work remotely, or in the office. Our goal is to help you and your team work effectively and collaboratively together to produce results that matter. 
 
As Brock Solutions continues to grow and respond to the on-going requirements of major clients, we need to add talent to our base of outstanding professionals. We are currently seeking a  Junior IT Support Specialist  to join our team of experienced professionals located at office in Irving, TX. 
 
 Why Work For Brock? 
 Competitive compensation package Profit sharing Continuous career growth Mentorship program Flexible working hours Company events and celebrations Travel opportunities Be resourceful to ensure that we meet contractual requirements and customer expectations 
What you'll do 
 Provide first level technical support for incoming requests from internal users 
 Assist users with the installation, configuration, and usage of desktop computers, peripheral equipment and software within established standards and guidelines 
 Actively troubleshoot technical problems, escalating as required 
 Working with other members of the IT organization to ensure timely resolution of issues 
 Take a leadership role in asset inventory control and deployment 
Qualifications Required:
 What You Bring to This Role 
 Superior customer service skills, professional and courteous 
 Attention to detail and committed to a high degree of accuracy in following standard processes 
 Aptitude to quickly learn new systems and technologies 
 In-depth knowledge of Microsoft Windows 10 and Microsoft Office 
 3-year college diploma in Information Technology, Computer Systems, Desktop Support or similar 
Nice-to-haves 
Knowledge in the following: 
 Wired and wireless network technologies 
 Desktop imaging and deployment technologies 
 Microsoft 365 applications and services 
Other Job Information (if applicable):
